and Paralympics generated 1.44 million tonnes of climate-warming carbon dioxide, from the food athletes ate and construction of their rooms to flights that spectators took and energy that powered events.\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 406}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's Olympics\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympics\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 465}, {\"ngram\": \"1.44 million tonnes\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"climate-warming carbon dioxide\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"the food athletes\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"their rooms\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 589}, {\"ngram\": \"flights\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 616}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a French government carbon-impact calculator, 1.44 million tonnes of CO2 is equivalent to driving a car 182,675 times around the globe or 898,305 return flights between Paris and New York.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 837, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999981997462, \"rank\": 1.6953161736991322e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a French government carbon-impact calculator\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 712}, {\"ngram\": \"1.44 million tonnes\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 733},